    <item>
      <title>Blog: The OtterConnect project is launched!</title>
      <link>/blog/2023/01/01/the-otterconnect-project-is-launched/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 01 Jan 2023 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>/blog/2023/01/01/the-otterconnect-project-is-launched/</guid>
      <description>
        
        
        
        <![CDATA[<img src="/blog/2023/01/01/the-otterconnect-project-is-launched/featured-logo-get%20copie_hu422e75f38a5896bd297cccc588552204_92671_640x0_resize_catmullrom_3.png" width="640" height="121"/>]]>
        
        &lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;OtterConnect&lt;/code&gt; project is launched with the support of &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.montpellier.fr/&#34;&gt;Montpellier city&lt;/a&gt;, de  &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.montpellier3m.fr/&#34;&gt;Montpellier Méditerranée Métropole&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.umontpellier.fr/&#34;&gt;University of Montpellier&lt;/a&gt; via &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.labex-cemeb.org/&#34;&gt;Labex Cemeb&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In the &lt;code&gt;OtterConnect&lt;/code&gt; project, we study connectivity on rivers in the Montpellier area (Hérault, Lez, Vidourle, Orb/Libron, Or), with the European otter (&lt;em&gt;Lutra lutra&lt;/em&gt;) as a case study, and as an indicator of green and blue infrastructures. We use non-invasive monitoring methods such as environmental DNA, camera trapping, spraint collection, statistical modeling and social sciences.&lt;/p&gt;







